<br>
NINE pages for statements, whines and insults about pretend items paid for with pretend cash... It is not real, just things in a game. You don’t need that money to eat, to pay your rent/mortgage or buy yourself a night out at the movies with your partner. But that is just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Oh, right... what am I thinking? This is the Soapbox, where people come crying about stupid crap they should be grown up enough to deal with themselves.<br>
<br>
Now that my slam against this damned place, yes, this stupid “whinebox”, is dealt with, I will endeavour to be more contolled. &lt;smirks&gt;<br>
<br>
Yes, Sabrosia could have dealt with the issue more diplomatically, and I am not happy with the light that has been cast upon the Daughters with this. However, it is Sabrosia’s right to bitch about overinflated prices, it is her right to tell the vendor to get stuffed with his greed. It was 35K now... what would it be in two weeks if the greedy realize that if they can sell for that price, how about bumping it up to 40K?<br>
<br>
There is no Better Business Bureau, or other regulatory authority, here in EQ, no place to go complain that a business is being ridiculous. It is up to the players themselves, us, to police this. In the real world, if a business is ripping people off, they get dealt with severely, yes?<br>
<br>
The “don’t like it, don’t buy it” policy works great, just like the “putting your head in the sand and pretend it doesn’t exist” policy. But some people like to take an active approach, shout out about something that they disagree with. Some take active approaches, others choose to ignore. &lt;shrugs&gt; To each their own.<br>
<br>
It has already been shown that Jadin was overselling his items, or at least having them at the highest end of the pricing spectrum, and that Sabrosia acted a bit harsher that necessary. Is this worth these nine pages of slander, insults and anger? It is just a game after all.<br>
<br>
As for the comment about Clan Werre... With myself in the capacity of the Black Witch of the Daughters Nocturnae’s Inner Circle, I will apologize for the slander of Clan Werre by a member of the Daughters Nocturnae. We have never had an issue with them, nor would I like to have one begin. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/baddog117/vivirose.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
